&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eastbourne District General Hospital&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Same Day Emergency Care&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;7 Day Service&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Same Day Emergency Care Unit is a hub of activity we provide the key to safe effective patient treatment and flow. We have varied pathways covering a wide variety of Emergency Medical Conditions. Our aim is to provide seamless, high quality care for patients using our service. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We pride ourselves on having a friendly and welcoming team – both Nursing and Medical – where you never feel alone and you get the support that you need. We also work very closely with our colleagues from the Acute Medical Unit and specialist services. If you are looking for an exciting and challenging role developing your acute medical clinical skills, learning new life skills, meeting new people and having a positive impact on patient experience – this is the opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are offering an interesting and varied role where you will be working as part of a friendly team which can provide you with the opportunity to develop your leadership and clinical skills in the field of acute medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours are 08.00-20.00 over 7 days including bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Revalidation Support/Regular Appraisals&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Educational support –&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Career Progression for both Trained Nurses and HCAs&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further information or an informal discussion, please contact Sharon Andrews- Lead Nurse&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt; – &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Same Day Emergency Care on 03001315384 or 0300 131 4500 ext 134012&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
